5:
That medical camp is around here,
right? What's the group called
again? Up something?
9:
The Updaters... Just like the name
implies, they've been trying to
change society since the
Administrator died.
13:
Well, I don't buy it. They're all
buddy-buddy with that con artist,
right?
16:
Well... I certainly hope no one like
Regis is there...
21:
Ah! Organic life-forms! Real organic
life-forms, in the flesh!
23:
You're just as Regis described!
Remarkable! I can't believe you're
real!
26:
A-are you the doctor of this camp?
Regis asked us to bring these parts.
31:
Ah, pardon me. I am Medic
Maintainer, but you may call me
Mech.
34:
But never mind that! May I please
inspect your insides?!
38:
I promise I'll put everything back in
its correct position! Please! Just a
peek!
43: Huh?! Wait, can we please NOT?!
48:
Yeah, there was no way a pal of
Regis's wasn't gonna be weird...
52:
Thank you for your help. With these
parts, I can finally give proper
treatment to my patients.
55:
Up until now, I've only been able to
administer emergency first aid with
junk parts.
58:
Junk parts? That doesn't sound
safe...
61:
I do not have much choice. If the
patient is dysfunctional for too long,
they'll forget how to move.
64:
That being said, it is technically
illegal. Ahaha...
69:
And while you're breakin' the law,
might as well slice us up like rats
too, huh?
74:
I truly am sorry about before! I was
just so excited that it slipped out!
78:
But surely you can't blame me when
your bodies are right in front of me,
just waiting to be studied!
80:
Could I take a sample from your
fluid storage devi—
I mean, a sample of your blood?
88:
W-well, he also doesn't seem like a
bad person. He's even treating
people free of charg—
93:
Y-y-you! You're Medic Maintainer,
aren't you?
95:
My apologies, but you must wait
your turn for your examination.
98:
I ain't no patient! I'm part of the
Updaters, and I'm here to shut you
down! Permanently!
100:
Why? He's treating you guys, ain't
he? Pretty sure that's called an ally.
103:
He ain't no ally! He's been treatin' the
Defaulters too! H-he's a traitor!
106:
I will always treat the injured,
regardless of their affiliation.
108:
...I'd even treat a headstrong fool like
you.
110:
D-d-don't you dare... make fun of
meee!
118:
A great doctor's surgical skills can
do far more than just treat patients.
120:
They also don't discriminate when it
comes to those they treat.
126:
Heh... Perhaps I should move you
into a body less capable of such
ruckus.
130: Well, that was quite the ordeal.
133:
To think I'd become a wanted man
and a target of the Updaters... It
seems I'll have to go into hiding for a
while.
136:
That's a lot for one person to handle,
if you ask me. You gonna be okay?
139:
Who know? But these things tend to
work themselves out.
144:
Well, why don't you come with us?
You'd have to go to another world
though.
149:
C-could I?! Surely there are plenty of
organic life-forms there as well,
correct?!
153:
...You know you can't dissect them,
right?
166:
Well, I suppose I can live with that.
This is a once-in-a-lifetime chance
to study organic life-forms, after all...
170:
We'll set off once I finish examining
the rest of the patients!
173: Oh my! This is just so... Hehehe.
